<plot>In a sun lit room two young girls find unexpected intimacy while playing in their blanket fort. Driven from the safety of their fort by a fire, the girls search for shelter to wash away the inflected wounds. Krisina Willemse's 'Little Sheep' describes the feelings of fear, love, and protection that are common in the liminal space of adolescents.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?338480</url></doc>
